# Key errors
E3000 = The key does not exist.
E3001 = The key has been revoked.
E3002 = The key algorithm is not supported.
E3003 = The certificate must be a valid PEM-encoded X.509 certificate.
E3004 = The key type is not valid for this operation.
E3005 = A certificate can only be attached to an asymmetric key.
